Detailed Description

Implements list data structure.

This class is not used directly. List should use instead.

See also:
List
 // Create a ListImpl and a node pointer as a list operator.
 ListImpl lst_impl(sizeof(int), HAS_TRIVIAL_CTOR);
 Node* target = lst_impl.acquireFirstNode();
 
 // Inserts node
 int a = 2011;
 target = lst_impl.insertNodeAt(target, a);
 
 // Removes node
 lst_impl.removeNodeAt(target);

Node* gaia::base::ListImpl::mpMiddle [private]

The access point of a list.

Because the list is constructed as a circular bi-directional linkedlist, each node is linked forward and backward to others. This node is set in the middle of a list and plays the role of access point of a list. This node is also regarded as the tail of a list.
